subject: Re: Spelling question
msgSnippet: You should always spell words as they re pronounced.  So, you could spell it /wenzdE/.  It might also be noteworthy that some people say /wednzdE/, but
messageBody:
You should always spell words as they're pronounced. So, you could
spell it /wenzdE/. It might also be noteworthy that some people
say /wednzdE/, but sounding the /d/ here produces one of the most
aweful and difficult consonant clusters I've ever seen in English.

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "lyleraymond"
<lyleraymond@y...> wrote:
>
>
> How do I spell "Wednesday" in junior/senior qs? As it is written,
> i.e. "Wed-nes-day," or as it is pronounced, i.e. "Wenzday?"
